hing I learned is that people should ask about loot, and/or you should make it clear up front beforehand.  Ambiguity doesnt work,  be clear, if they ask spell it out. <br>
<br>
People do play this game for fun , think about yourself. Is organizing them raids and such fun? It wasn't really for me, I tried to help people have fun and an easy time. And learn. And get loot.<br>
<br>
People play this game for a variety of reasons, but I know NO ONE that doesnt appreciate getting some loot once in a while. Especially dragon god loot or up. It is very cool I think to get something off  a dragon. Some of us older players, hey its no big whup, god loot yawn. Been there done that, dont play for that anymore. <br>
<br>
Let me say again, people play for loot. That isnt their all consuming reason for playing, but why go on xx raid if you have no chance at loot? I mean sooner or later, Im going to want something. It doesnt make me greedy, I am just trying to upgrade or better myself. If I have to wait my turn, fine. If i need to pay some dues, fine. But eventually I am going to want something better than what I have. Everyone feels the same, and it does NOT make them greedy.<br>
<br>
I used to rant and rave about loot, heck there were days when you raiding pof and after a few lost lvls and many lost hrs sleep, you clear the plane, and ONE piece of armor would drop. Not one per class, but ONE after a raid. Well, that happened once but 2-4 pieces per raid was the norm once.  We werent doing it for fun, thats for sure, it was torture. Basically we were paying our dues, paying the price for being &quot;l33t&quot;. We were after loot. Better armor. And we werent greedy.<br>
<br>
So take pride in organizing raids and learning thru experience and hardship, stress and death. No one is taking anything away from you. Have a loot system in place, this is going to xx and xx. But if it is OPEN raids, the loot needs to be open to a degree. If it is a raid for someones scale, then the scale goes to them, but if the raid is formed by hodge podge methods, or announcing all zones, open raid...then the loot should be OPEN for all. <br>
<br>
The organizer/leader must be firm, fair, consistent. They must be understanding, patient, knowledgabe. They need to be respected, have a certain degree of notoriety, or be well known as it were, and above all once again be PATIENT. You will find yourself repeating yourself countless times. You will be flamed no matter how fair and clear you are/were. You will be asked, &quot;what about me?&quot; or &quot;:what loot?&quot;. <br>
<br>
People play for loot. get over it. I certainly enjoy getting new stuff. Just be patient and help others in this game, heck in life. We all arent the same, and well...<br>
<br>
I started my younger brothers in eq a few yrs ago. They only played for a few months, but Loevon sends me a tell one day, hey theres this guy claiming hes your brother asked me for a loan of xxthousand pp. My other brother made a female erud so he could get free stuff from guys. They were doing the same stuff I flamed people for all the time. I know my brothers are cool, and good guys, honest and all that. So I got to thinking....and stopped hating people for wanting loot.<br>
<br>
Being the guy in charge isnt easy, people always are ungrateful no matter what you do. Just strive to be firm, fair, and consistent.<br>
<br>
And pls stop the flames you all.<br>
<br>
Peace <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdrinal28133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tingteng>Tingteng</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.iconbazaar.com/dots/animated/14anidot5c.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=red><B>Dranalite</B></font></span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/29/02 3:55:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3896.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What you fail to ..</span><hr size=1> I'm done repeating myself. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
